Backend ↔ Frontend Connection Overview (Current State)
Architecture (Clean & Solid)

Frontend (pure vanilla JS) → never talks directly to HA.
All communication goes through /frontend/js/api.js → FastAPI backend (backend/api.py).
Backend handles:
Storage (storage.py — JSON files on disk)
HA communication (ha_client.py — WebSocket + caching)
Compilation

Data format: Piston JSON (with device_map, variables, nested statements, etc.)

Key Data Flows

Pistons (CRUD)
GET /pistons → list
GET /pistons/{id} → full JSON
POST /pistons + PUT /pistons/{id} → create/update
Backend does light validation (_validate_device_map) and adds timestamps/ID.

Devices (Wizard + Globals)
GET /devices → cached list from HA
GET /device/{entity_id}/capabilities and /services
This is likely where your "only takes 1 device" issue lives.

Globals
Separate store (globals.json)
Device-type globals support multiple entities (array).

Compile/Deploy
POST /pistons/{id}/compile → returns YAML + errors/warnings
Context builder + Jinja templates


